#ident	"@(#)oamintf:syssetup/Help	1.1"

TITLE:System Name, Date/Time and Initial Password Setup

ABSTRACT:
	The subcommands in the "systemsetup" menu provide functions for
	setting up your computer.  They include the ability to tell
	the computer about its environment (date, time, and time zone),
	the ability to define which administrative and system capabilities
	require a password, the ability to set the machine's name and
	the network node name, and the ability to setup first login(s)
	for users (including password information).
